headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 21 points, 20 rebounds and nine assists as the Indiana Pacers strengthened their hold on a play-in tournament spot with a 111-102 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers beat Cavaliers 111-102, move into ninth place in East

headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook broke Oscar Robertson's 47-year-old NBA record for triple-doubles and missed a potential game-winning 3-pointer as the Washington Wizards lost 125-124 to the Atlanta Hawks on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Westbrook breaks Robinson's record as Wizards fall to Hawks

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Dillon Brooks scored 23 points, Jonas Valanciunas had 20 points, 11 rebounds and five blocks, and the Memphis Grizzlies secured a spot the postseason play-in tournament by beating the New Orleans Pelicans 115-110 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies beat Pelicans 115-110, secure play-in spot

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan had 23 points and the San Antonio Spurs set a franchise record for points in the first half while rolling to a 146-125 victory over the Milwaukee Bucks on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs' record-setting 1st half ends Bucks' streak, 146-125

events.name: Utah Jazz at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry made a go-ahead 3-pointer with 14 seconds left, moments after missing from deep, and scored 36 points to lead the Golden State Warriors past the Western Conference-leading Utah Jazz 119-116 on Monday night to keep hold of the eighth...
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry's late 3 lifts Warriors past Jazz 119-116

events.name: Houston Rockets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 34 points and nine rebounds, and the Portland Trail Blazers raced to a 140-129 victory over the Houston Rockets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard, Blazers score 50 in first, blast Rockets 140-129
